LLM-based Agent Composition
LLM-based Agent Composition is a blog post by Lilian Weng that identifies memory as a critical component in agent systems.

AiGC Interview Guide
AiGC Interview Guide is the source document for the article discussing 8 optimization methods for long-term memory in multi-turn dialogues.

Lilian Weng
Lilian Weng is the OpenAI AI Application Research Lead who authored the blog "LLM-based Agent Composition" which identifies memory as a key component.

ConversationEntityMemory
ConversationEntityMemory is a method that extracts and remembers key entities and their relationships from dialogue history, applicable in legal consultation scenarios.

ConversationBufferMemory
ConversationBufferMemory is a method that retains the entire dialogue history, useful in customer service scenarios for maintaining context across multiple topics.

LangChain
LangChain is a framework that provides code implementations for 8 different memory maintenance methods in various scenarios.

ConversationKGMemory
ConversationKGMemory is a method that builds a knowledge graph of entities and their relationships from dialogue history, useful in medical consultation scenarios.<SEP>A specific LLM conversation memory technique mentioned in the document's additional content.

ConversationBufferWindowMemory
ConversationBufferWindowMemory is a method that uses a sliding window to retain only the most recent interactions, beneficial for focused responses in e-commerce consultations.<SEP>A specific LLM conversation memory technique mentioned in the document's additional content.

ConversationSummaryMemory
ConversationSummaryMemory is a method that summarizes previous tutoring content and student questions to provide targeted explanations and exercises.<SEP>ConversationSummaryMemory is a method that summarizes previous dialogue stages and student questions, applicable in educational tutoring scenarios.

Telecom Company Customer Service
Telecom Company Customer Service is an example scenario where ConversationBufferMemory helps maintain complete dialogue history for coherent service.

E-commerce Platform
E-commerce Platform is an example scenario where ConversationBufferWindowMemory helps focus on recent product and delivery questions.

Legal Consultation
Legal Consultation is an example scenario where ConversationEntityMemory helps remember case names, legal provisions, and personal information.

Medical Consultation
Medical Consultation is an example scenario where ConversationKGMemory helps build knowledge graphs of symptoms and medical history.

Educational Tutoring
Educational Tutoring is an example scenario where ConversationSummaryMemory helps summarize previous tutoring content and student questions.

Xiao Li
Xiao Li is a programmer mentioned in the example code for ConversationKGMemory demonstration.

Mo Er Suo
Mo Er Suo is the pen name of Xiao Li and the author of the WeChat public account "LLM Application Full Stack Development".

LLM Application Full Stack Development
LLM Application Full Stack Development is a WeChat public account authored by Mo Er Suo.

8 Optimization Methods For Long-Term Memory
8 Optimization Methods For Long-Term Memory is the main topic of the article discussing different approaches to maintain memory in multi-turn dialogues.

OpenAI
OpenAI is the organization where Lilian Weng serves as AI Application Research Lead.

ChatOpenAI
ChatOpenAI is an implementation using the GPT-3.5-turbo model with temperature 0, used in the ConversationEntityMemory example.

GPT-3.5-turbo
GPT-3.5-turbo is the specific model used in the ChatOpenAI implementation for ConversationEntityMemory.

Customer Service Chatbot
Customer Service Chatbot is a specific application scenario mentioned for telecom companies using ConversationBufferMemory.

Bill Inquiry
Bill Inquiry is an example topic in customer service dialogues where users ask about billing issues.

Network Connection Issues
Network Connection Issues is an example topic in customer service dialogues where users ask about network problems.

Product Consultation
Product Consultation is an example scenario in e-commerce platforms where users ask about specific products.

Battery Life
Battery Life is an example product feature mentioned in e-commerce consultations about mobile phones.

Delivery Methods
Delivery Methods is an example topic in e-commerce consultations about shipping options.
is a programmer who uses the pen name.
is the pen name used by.

ConversationSummaryBufferMemory
ConversationSummaryBufferMemory is a method that retains detailed information from recent interactions while providing summaries of historical problem handling.

ConversationTokenBufferMemory
ConversationTokenBufferMemory is a method that focuses on the most recent and critical questions to avoid information confusion.

VectorStoreRetrieverMemory
VectorStoreRetrieverMemory is a method that quickly retrieves the most relevant information from a large amount of historical data.<SEP>VectorStoreRetrieverMemory is an AI conversation memory mechanism discussed in the document for applications like financial consultation chatbots.

Chroma
Chroma is a vector store used with an embedding function for retrieval.

OpenAIEmbeddings
OpenAIEmbeddings is an embedding function used for vector storage and retrieval.

PromptTemplate
PromptTemplate is a template used to structure the conversation prompt with history and input variables.

ConversationChain
ConversationChain is a conversational AI chain that uses a language model, prompt, and memory for dialogue.

Educational Tutoring Scenario
Educational Tutoring Scenario involves students asking different math problems or comprehension difficulties, such as understanding quadratic equations.

Technical Support Scenario
Technical Support Scenario involves handling long-term technical issues like software troubleshooting with various error messages and feedback.

Financial Advisory Scenario
Financial Advisory Scenario involves clients asking multiple questions about investments, market trends, or personal financial planning.

News Event Understanding
News Event Understanding involves users asking questions about specific news events, such as important decisions from an economic summit.

Quadratic Equations
Quadratic Equations are mathematical problems mentioned as an example of student comprehension difficulties in the Educational Tutoring Scenario.

Software Fault Troubleshooting
Software Fault Troubleshooting is a long-term technical problem mentioned in the Technical Support Scenario involving various error messages and feedback.

Stock Market Trends
Stock Market Trends are mentioned as a topic of client questions in the Financial Advisory Scenario regarding recent market movements.

Investment Portfolio Allocation
Investment Portfolio Allocation is mentioned as a client concern in the Financial Advisory Scenario about how to distribute investments.

Economic Summit
Economic Summit is a specific news event mentioned where users might ask about important decisions made.

Hot Pot
Hot Pot is mentioned as a food preference in the example conversation context saved to memory.

Wrestling Matches
Wrestling Matches are mentioned as a disliked activity in the example conversation context saved to memory.

Knowledge Planet
Knowledge Planet appears as an organization name at the end of the text.<SEP>Knowledge Planet is a knowledge-sharing platform, indicated by the Chinese characters '' in the logo.
